        "auditory": "I hear speech that starts, revises, and starts again—half-questions, little “wait—” sounds, the cadence of someone checking their own assumptions.",
        "tactile": "Someone's body holds a searching tension—still, but not relaxed, like their attention is reaching for something it can’t quite grasp."
